                            <item xml:id="e3">
                              <locus target = "#60v"/>
                              <desc>Two marginal symbols surrounded by a line in alternating red and ‎black dots mark the midpoint of the psalms.‎
                                </desc>
                                </item>

                            <item xml:id = "e4">
                              <locus target ="#150v"/>
                                <desc type = "OwnershipNote">Note of ownership: Aläqa Ṭäga, <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አለቃ፡ ጠጋ፡</foreign>; and scrawls. ‎</desc>
                                </item>

                            <item xml:id = "e5">
                              <locus target = "#ms_i1.1"/>
                              <desc>‎7.‎	Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters.‎</desc>
                              </item>

                            <item xml:id = "e6">
                              <desc>Columetric layout of texts <locus target = "#114v"/>(Ps. 150)<locus from = "123r" to ="123v"/> (tenth biblical canticle).</desc>
                              </item>

                            <item xml:id = "e7">
                              <desc>Numbered quires 1-10</desc>
                              </item>

                            <item xml:id = "e8">
                              <desc>
                                ‎Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly <locus target = "#35r #‎‎64r #131r"/>);
                                and lines of text are written interlinearly <locus target = "#111r"/>);
                                and in ‎the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the ‎text is to be inserted <locus target = "#30r"/>, line 3; <locus target ="#54v"/>, line 7);
                                erasure markings ‎are visible <locus target = "#30r"/>, line 3; <locus target ="#47v"/>, line 10; <locus target ="#50r"/>, line 3; <locus target ="#52r"/>, line 6; <locus target ="#78v"/>, ‎line 14; <locus target ="#88r"/>, line 8, 14 and 22; <locus target ="#89v"/>, line 14; etc.);
                                text has been ‎removed <locus target ="#53v"/>, line 16).‎
                              </desc>
                              </item>

                            <item xml:id="e9">
                              <desc>
                                ‎The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. ‎Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                                ‎appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate ‎script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                                the scribe ‎completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout).‎
                              </desc>
                              </item>


                        </list>
                      </additions>


